# --- Contact form delivery -------------------------------------------------
# The form at /contact needs this to reach an inbox. Without it, the form does not
# pretend: it tells the visitor the message was NOT sent and shows the mailto address.
#
# Get a free key at https://web3forms.com — enter tenzok.tech@gmail.com and they
# email you the access key. Then set it here (in .env.local locally, and in the
# Vercel project's Environment Variables for production).
#
# Why NEXT_PUBLIC_ (i.e. why the key is exposed to the browser):
# Web3Forms sits behind Cloudflare bot protection. A server-side fetch — from Node,
# a Next.js server action, curl, anything without a browser TLS fingerprint — gets a
# 403 "Just a moment..." challenge page. Verified: the identical request returns 200
# from a browser and 403 from Node. So the submission MUST come from the browser, and
# the key must be public. This is Web3Forms' intended model; their own documented
# snippet puts the key in a hidden input in the page HTML. The key only authorises
# "send mail to the address it is registered to". If it is ever abused, rotate it in
# the Web3Forms dashboard and enable their spam protection.
NEXT_PUBLIC_WEB3FORMS_ACCESS_KEY=
